VAn A-grade vocalist of AIR, Manda Sudharani, a widely recognised performer vocal concerts in and outside the country, was honoured at Kalabharathi last week. Her students organised the event as a mark of gratitude.Grand ceremonyIt was accomplished by aptly-chosen guests of honour. They were Sudharani's preceptor, violinist and vocalist Sreeman Ivaturi Vijayeswara Rao. He was a disciple of the late Dwaram Narasinga Rao Naidu. The other was the exquisite exponent of Carnatic music on the violin, Dwaram Durga Prasada Rao, the worthy son of late Narasinga Rao Naidu. Compere of the event, Perala Balamurali Krishna, was poetic in describing how the event turned out to be a ceremonious adoration of the admirable line of continuity of the tradition of tutor and the taught (guru parampara) relationship.Dwaram Durga Prasada Rao spoke highly of Sudha's father, late A.V. Ramana Murty, in particular how Sudha made his dreams come true by getting successfully stamped as an A grade vocalist of AIR and a widely recognised exponent of Carnatic vocal even before he attained liberation rather early.Her guru, Vijayeswara Rao, elaborated on why he cherished Sudha as a soul-fulfilling gem of a God-given gift.Sudharani expressed her grateful happiness by way of rendering a short vocal concert. She was accompanied on the violin by her guru Vijayeswara Rao, on mridangam by V.V. Ramana Murty, and kanjeera by M. Ravi. In praise of her guru, she sang Tatwameruga Tharama (Garudadhwani), Padavi Nee Satbhakthi (Saalagabhairavi) and Paramaatmudu Velige (Vaagadheeswari) besides Ragam, Thanam Pallavi in Kalyani in Trisranada Aditaalam and splendidly concluded a Balamurali thillana.
